*παῖς / pais / paheece
*Perhaps from [[παίω]] {{GG|3817}}; a boy (as often beaten with impunity), or (by analogy) a girl, and (generally) a child; specifically a slave or servant (especially a minister to a king; and by eminence to God): - child, maid (-en), (man) servant, son, young man.